\f1\fs28 \cf4 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
I
\f0 n Linux, Logical Volume Manager is a device mapper framework that provides logical volume management for the Linux kernel. Most modern Linux distributions are LVM-aware to the point of being able to have their root file systems on a logical volume.
\fs32 \cf0 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \
